    "duration": "3:35",
    "audience": [
      "Adults"
    ],
    "description": "Control in conversations doesn’t always come from being direct. Sometimes it happens quietly — through tone, positioning, and subtle shifts in expectations. What begins as a clear agreement can slowly turn into a situation where you feel pressured to accommodate, adjust, or accept less than what was originally defined. This guided reflection explores how power shifts happen in professional and personal interactions, especially when someone reframes the dynamic without saying it outright. Learn how to recognise when agreements are being replaced by unspoken pressure — and how to restore clarity without conflict. If you’ve ever felt like someone you hired or worked with subtly changed the terms, this will help you hold your position and bring the conversation back to structure. Agreements define position — not tone.",
