    "id": "why-chasing-people-lowers-your-value-2",
    "title": "Why Chasing People Lowers Your Value",
    "duration": "5:15",
    "audience": [
      "Professionals"
    ],
    "description": "Do you find yourself constantly checking for replies, overthinking interactions, replaying conversations, or emotionally chasing people, opportunities, or outcomes? This guided visualization explores the hidden emotional cost of over-pursuit and what happens when your nervous system starts attaching your worth to external validation. Through a psychologically grounded cognitive simulation, you’ll learn how to: stop emotionally overreaching, recognise “validation drift” in real time, regulate anxious pursuit, stay grounded while waiting, and reconnect with your own center without becoming cold or detached. This is not about playing games, pretending not to care, or becoming emotionally unavailable. It is about learning how to: desire without collapsing, care without chasing, and remain internally steady while uncertainty still exists.",
